1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,700
Grace be unto you, and peace from God our Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ. Amen.

2
00:00:07,600 --> 00:00:11,620
Let us hear the word of God, our regular epistolary lesson for this Sunday,

3
00:00:12,140 --> 00:00:16,620
as we find it written in Paul's letter to the Romans, beginning there in the sixth chapter,

4
00:00:17,180 --> 00:00:19,060
especially the third verse.

5
00:00:19,780 --> 00:00:26,080
Know ye not that so many of us as were baptized into Jesus Christ

6
00:00:26,080 --> 00:00:29,580
were baptized into his death.

7
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:37,460
And now may the words of my mouth and the meditations of our hearts be acceptable in thy sight.

8
00:00:37,460 --> 00:00:41,100
O Lord, our strength and our Redeemer. Amen.

9
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:49,920
In Christ Jesus, the Lord of our Christian life,

10
00:00:50,060 --> 00:00:52,940
dear friends, you who are here in God's house this morning,

11
00:00:52,940 --> 00:00:58,120
and you also, Christian friends, who are worshiping with us by means of the radio.

12
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:04,440
Today, as you know, is the sixth Sunday after the Festival of Trinity.

13
00:01:05,340 --> 00:01:09,040
It is our custom on these After Trinity Sundays

14
00:01:09,040 --> 00:01:16,360
to deal with some of the common and practical problems of our Christian life and conduct.

15
00:01:16,760 --> 00:01:20,220
You recall that last Sunday we talked about getting along with one another,

16
00:01:20,220 --> 00:01:23,300
how to live in peace and harmony with one another.

17
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:28,120
And today we have a very practical thing that we want to talk about,

18
00:01:28,420 --> 00:01:33,180
and that is the matter of carelessness in our Christian life.

19
00:01:33,580 --> 00:01:37,760
I like to call it sloppy Christian living.

20
00:01:38,560 --> 00:01:40,360
Sloppy Christian living.

21
00:01:41,140 --> 00:01:44,560
This kind of living where we're off the beam.

22
00:01:45,020 --> 00:01:48,740
We're either always to the left or we're always to the right,

23
00:01:48,740 --> 00:01:53,200
but in our Christian life, it is a sloppy thing.

24
00:01:53,420 --> 00:01:54,800
It's a careless thing.

25
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,220
It is an inferior thing.

26
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:03,340
It is a Christian life that is not becoming us as Christians.

27
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:06,580
And you know, friends, it's a very easy thing

28
00:02:06,580 --> 00:02:10,820
to slip into a sloppy Christian life, isn't it?

29
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:13,700
It's very easy to look at our life

30
00:02:13,700 --> 00:02:17,000
and to not care whether we are doing the will of God

31
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,640
or whether we are not doing it.

32
00:02:18,700 --> 00:02:21,800
Not to care whether as we look at our life

33
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:24,140
that it's a soggy thing

34
00:02:24,140 --> 00:02:27,420
and that it's something that we are rather ashamed of.

35
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:30,640
And it may all come very easily from this thing

36
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:32,980
that we say something like this to ourselves.

37
00:02:33,100 --> 00:02:37,280
Now we are saved by the forgiving grace of God, are we not?

38
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:38,940
And that's true, isn't it?

39
00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:40,920
We are saved by the grace of God

40
00:02:40,920 --> 00:02:44,660
and that means that you and I are not saved by our life.

41
00:02:44,700 --> 00:02:45,540
Isn't that right?

42
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,560
And because we are saved by the forgiving grace of God

43
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:51,940
and that our lives do not save us,

44
00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:53,520
it's the easiest thing in the world,

45
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:55,220
especially for us Lutherans,

46
00:02:55,560 --> 00:02:59,000
to get the idea that life, therefore, is not very important.

47
00:02:59,440 --> 00:03:01,420
Because if life doesn't save,

48
00:03:01,540 --> 00:03:02,880
what's the difference how I live?

49
00:03:03,260 --> 00:03:04,520
What's the difference, therefore,

50
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,180
whether my Christian life is sloppy,

51
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,580
whether it doesn't measure up,

52
00:03:07,580 --> 00:03:09,760
whether it's absolutely inferior,

53
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:11,320
whether it's the kind of a life

54
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:13,520
that is not becoming me as a Christian,

55
00:03:13,860 --> 00:03:14,880
what's the difference?

56
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,060
After all, isn't it foolishness

57
00:03:17,060 --> 00:03:19,300
to live on the beam

58
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,280
when we are not saved by our life?

59
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:24,420
Some of us may even draw this conclusion.

60
00:03:24,940 --> 00:03:25,600
We may say,

61
00:03:25,720 --> 00:03:27,160
why, the thing that we ought to do

62
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:30,080
is to go out and to sing to our heart's content

63
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:32,220
because the more we sin,

64
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,920
the more we show the world

65
00:03:33,920 --> 00:03:36,880
how great is the forgiving grace of God.

66
00:03:36,880 --> 00:03:38,680
If we go out and kill

67
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,240
and live in adultery and murder,

68
00:03:40,680 --> 00:03:41,980
why, the world would say,

69
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:44,200
my, how tremendously best

70
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,340
is the grace of God that forgives

71
00:03:47,340 --> 00:03:50,760
and actually we would be glorifying grace.

72
00:03:51,460 --> 00:03:54,960
That's the way some Christians sometimes feel

73
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:57,260
about their Christian life.

74
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:58,460
And that's why today

75
00:03:58,460 --> 00:04:01,180
we want to talk about this thing

76
00:04:01,180 --> 00:04:02,220
of carelessness,

77
00:04:02,960 --> 00:04:04,020
of indifference,

78
00:04:04,300 --> 00:04:06,760
of sloppy Christian living.

79
00:04:07,440 --> 00:04:09,220
Doesn't it make any difference

80
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:11,100
even though we are saved

81
00:04:11,100 --> 00:04:13,260
by the saving grace of God

82
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:15,900
and our lives do not save us?

83
00:04:16,400 --> 00:04:17,560
The speaker this morning

84
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,620
from the Word of God

85
00:04:18,620 --> 00:04:20,120
is the Apostle Paul,

86
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:20,980
the little Jew

87
00:04:20,980 --> 00:04:22,960
from up in Tarsus in Cilicia,

88
00:04:23,440 --> 00:04:24,340
the great war horse

89
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:25,360
of the Christian church.

90
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,560
And we find him writing

91
00:04:26,560 --> 00:04:28,560
to his Christian congregation at Rome.

92
00:04:28,960 --> 00:04:29,640
And yet then,

93
00:04:29,900 --> 00:04:30,960
when he had spoken to them

94
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:32,060
about the very fact

95
00:04:32,060 --> 00:04:32,840
that we are saved

96
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,340
by the forgiving grace of God,

97
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,880
and there was a danger

98
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:37,520
that because they would know

99
00:04:37,520 --> 00:04:38,340
that they were saved

100
00:04:38,340 --> 00:04:39,460
by the mercy of God

101
00:04:39,460 --> 00:04:40,400
in Christ Jesus

102
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,620
and not by their lives,

103
00:04:41,980 --> 00:04:42,860
that somehow or other

104
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:43,920
they would get the idea

105
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:44,940
that the Christian life

106
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:45,840
is not important

107
00:04:45,840 --> 00:04:47,260
and that they would go out

108
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:47,560
and say,

109
00:04:47,660 --> 00:04:49,240
now I can sin to my heart's content.

110
00:04:49,360 --> 00:04:50,460
It doesn't make any difference.

111
00:04:50,760 --> 00:04:51,200
And therefore,

112
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,720
I do not have to avoid

113
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:53,960
being off of the beam.

114
00:04:54,360 --> 00:04:55,600
And so he wrote to them

115
00:04:55,600 --> 00:04:56,600
as he speaks to you

116
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:57,640
and me this morning,

117
00:04:58,060 --> 00:04:58,840
assuring us

118
00:04:58,840 --> 00:04:59,940
that we are saved

119
00:04:59,940 --> 00:05:01,520
by the forgiving grace of God

120
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:02,140
to be sure.

121
00:05:02,540 --> 00:05:03,280
Assuring us

122
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:03,880
that you and I

123
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,560
are not saved by our lives

124
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:06,740
and but therefore

125
00:05:06,740 --> 00:05:08,040
telling and calling

126
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,240
to us as Christians

127
00:05:09,240 --> 00:05:11,620
to avoid being off of the beam,

128
00:05:12,080 --> 00:05:13,560
to avoid carelessness

129
00:05:13,560 --> 00:05:15,480
in a sloppy Christian life,

130
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,060
to avoid anything

131
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:18,680
that doesn't measure up

132
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:19,900
because this is what

133
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,280
he told the Christians at Rome,

134
00:05:21,560 --> 00:05:22,060
he says,

135
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,260
do you not know

136
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:24,620
that as many of us

137
00:05:24,620 --> 00:05:25,760
as were baptized

138
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:27,460
into Jesus Christ

139
00:05:27,460 --> 00:05:28,500
were baptized

140
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,240
into his death?

141
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,160
Do you not realize

142
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:33,700
that because you were baptized

143
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,460
into Christ's death

144
00:05:35,460 --> 00:05:36,620
that therefore

145
00:05:36,620 --> 00:05:38,040
you must avoid

146
00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:39,380
being off of the beam

147
00:05:39,380 --> 00:05:40,440
in your Christian life?

148
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:42,220
You've got to get rid

149
00:05:42,220 --> 00:05:44,120
of a sloppy Christian living.

150
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,780
You've got to get rid

151
00:05:45,780 --> 00:05:47,020
of that which is inferior.

152
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:49,880
You dare not be off of the beam.

153
00:05:50,180 --> 00:05:52,440
You've got to be on the beam

154
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,900
even though you are not

155
00:05:53,900 --> 00:05:54,920
saved by your life

156
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,580
because when you were baptized,

157
00:05:57,840 --> 00:05:58,780
do you not know

158
00:05:58,780 --> 00:05:59,960
that you were baptized

159
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:01,260
into his death?

160
00:06:01,720 --> 00:06:02,640
It's well this morning

161
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,900
as we are here in God's house

162
00:06:03,900 --> 00:06:05,180
to take a look at our baptism

163
00:06:05,180 --> 00:06:06,320
and to realize

164
00:06:06,320 --> 00:06:08,060
just what it has meant to us

165
00:06:08,060 --> 00:06:09,140
and what it means

166
00:06:09,140 --> 00:06:09,900
to be baptized

167
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,300
into Christ's death.

168
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:12,600
If there is anything

169
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:13,160
in the world

170
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,080
that ought to cause you

171
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:14,720
and me to avoid

172
00:06:14,720 --> 00:06:15,800
being off of the beam,

173
00:06:16,160 --> 00:06:18,660
to avoid sloppy Christian living,

174
00:06:18,660 --> 00:06:20,080
the kind of living

175
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:22,240
that just doesn't measure up,

176
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,560
it is not becoming

177
00:06:23,560 --> 00:06:24,380
you and me,

178
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:25,980
it ought to be this.

179
00:06:26,080 --> 00:06:26,940
We were baptized

180
00:06:26,940 --> 00:06:28,480
into Jesus Christ

181
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,840
and thus into his death

182
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:31,380
and that in the first place

183
00:06:31,380 --> 00:06:31,940
means this,

184
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:32,780
that when you and I

185
00:06:32,780 --> 00:06:33,460
were baptized

186
00:06:33,460 --> 00:06:35,040
and baptized into his death,

187
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:36,480
that means that we were

188
00:06:36,480 --> 00:06:38,180
joined to Christ's death,

189
00:06:38,580 --> 00:06:39,440
that death

190
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:40,820
which made it possible

191
00:06:40,820 --> 00:06:42,100
for the forgiving

192
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:43,640
grace of God

193
00:06:43,640 --> 00:06:44,420
to operate.

194
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,920
How many of us

195
00:06:45,920 --> 00:06:46,720
realize this,

196
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:47,460
that if Christ

197
00:06:47,460 --> 00:06:48,620
had not died,

198
00:06:49,140 --> 00:06:50,180
the grace of God

199
00:06:50,180 --> 00:06:50,980
could never

200
00:06:50,980 --> 00:06:52,340
have forgiven sin?

201
00:06:52,960 --> 00:06:53,820
Some people say,

202
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:55,520
well God is a forgiving God,

203
00:06:55,620 --> 00:06:56,180
he's gracious

204
00:06:56,180 --> 00:06:57,020
and he's merciful,

205
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,300
therefore God

206
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,020
can forgive sins easily,

207
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:01,020
but listen,

208
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,240
God himself

209
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:04,160
could not forgive sins

210
00:07:04,160 --> 00:07:05,360
had it not been

211
00:07:05,360 --> 00:07:05,920
for the death

212
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,300
of his son Jesus Christ.

213
00:07:07,740 --> 00:07:08,620
The second person

214
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:09,180
of the Trinity,

215
00:07:09,380 --> 00:07:09,980
God the Son,

216
00:07:10,060 --> 00:07:10,640
had to come out

217
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,100
of the ivory palaces

218
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,220
into this world of sin,

219
00:07:13,300 --> 00:07:14,180
become a human being

220
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:14,840
without sin

221
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:15,820
and he had to go

222
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:16,820
to Calvary's cross

223
00:07:16,820 --> 00:07:18,260
and there he had to die.

224
00:07:18,400 --> 00:07:18,600
Why?

225
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,040
Because God

226
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,600
is a God of grace

227
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:22,340
but he's also

228
00:07:22,340 --> 00:07:23,400
a God of justice

229
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:24,760
and being a God

230
00:07:24,760 --> 00:07:25,260
of justice

231
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:26,540
when the soul sins

232
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:27,580
and it's punishable

233
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:28,160
by death,

234
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,600
God must carry out

235
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:30,860
that verdict of justice

236
00:07:30,860 --> 00:07:31,860
and therefore

237
00:07:31,860 --> 00:07:32,860
for God

238
00:07:32,860 --> 00:07:33,860
to be merciful,

239
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:34,980
for God

240
00:07:34,980 --> 00:07:35,620
to forgive

241
00:07:35,620 --> 00:07:37,000
on the basis of grace,

242
00:07:37,160 --> 00:07:38,600
Christ had to die

243
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,880
and he had to meet

244
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:41,220
the justice of God

245
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,200
and you and I

246
00:07:42,200 --> 00:07:43,480
don't understand Calvary

247
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,420
until we stand there

248
00:07:44,420 --> 00:07:45,160
and say there was

249
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:45,800
God's Son

250
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,720
who willingly

251
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:47,580
met the justice

252
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:48,220
of God.

253
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,380
He on the cross

254
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,200
he bore the guilt

255
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:50,820
and the punishment

256
00:07:50,820 --> 00:07:51,360
of the world.

257
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:52,720
He endured the equal

258
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:53,440
of an eternity

259
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:54,020
in hell

260
00:07:54,020 --> 00:07:54,900
for the human race

261
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:55,940
and he met

262
00:07:55,940 --> 00:07:57,420
the justice of God

263
00:07:57,420 --> 00:07:58,800
so that by meeting

264
00:07:58,800 --> 00:08:00,000
God's justice

265
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,980
therefore it was possible

266
00:08:01,980 --> 00:08:02,720
for God

267
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,500
who is merciful

268
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,060
and gracious

269
00:08:04,060 --> 00:08:06,120
to have a forgiving grace

270
00:08:06,120 --> 00:08:07,140
and to forgive sins

271
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:07,940
and therefore

272
00:08:07,940 --> 00:08:08,740
when you and I

273
00:08:08,740 --> 00:08:09,360
were baptized

274
00:08:09,360 --> 00:08:10,940
we received

275
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,080
we were given

276
00:08:12,080 --> 00:08:13,760
this forgiving grace

277
00:08:13,760 --> 00:08:14,580
of God.

278
00:08:15,060 --> 00:08:15,700
How many of us

279
00:08:15,700 --> 00:08:16,960
realize that the greatest

280
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:17,740
thing that has ever

281
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:18,700
happened to you and me

282
00:08:18,700 --> 00:08:20,600
has been our baptism?

283
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:22,220
When in infancy

284
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,060
you and I

285
00:08:23,060 --> 00:08:23,600
were brought

286
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:24,740
by means of water

287
00:08:24,740 --> 00:08:25,880
and the word of God

288
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:26,720
in baptism

289
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:28,680
something tremendous

290
00:08:28,680 --> 00:08:29,480
happened

291
00:08:29,480 --> 00:08:30,940
and what happened

292
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:31,580
in baptism

293
00:08:31,580 --> 00:08:32,640
we were united

294
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,400
